Our storyBy Rosemarie WillettAbout 10 years ago I started Fiddlehead Farm, an idyllic roadside farm market for fresh local produce, fresh baked goods, gourmet ingredients, artisanal cheeses or just a great conversation. It was so much more than just a roadside farm stand. It was a place to connect with your friends, neighbors and strangers through food. Regulars were known on a first name basis. Fresh herbs were cut to order. Favorite recipes were jotted down and shared on a piece of butcher paper. Stories were shared behind the artisanal cheese maker or who dug out your potatoes this morning. People would hang out on the front porch long after they had finished their shopping and cup of coffee. Fiddlehead Farm captured the charm of the Vineyard: local living and a connection with your community and with your food!  This season - 2 years after we had closed our doors indefinitely - I had the opportunity to re-open the farm and market as North Tisbury Farm. New name, new coat of paint, but the same charming old farm, the same passion for clean and local food and the same devotion to our customers.  Our CommunityI had really missed the person to person connection through Fiddlehead Farm and, as it turns out, I was not alone! Over and over again we hear from our returning customers and new visitors how there is nothing like the feeling of traditional human connection when shopping for your food! The chance to bump into people you would otherwise never get to see, slowing down for face-to-face interactions, discovering something new about the food you are feeding your family or friends...In many cultures the local market is the center of the community, featuring familiar faces. This is exactly what inspired the concept for Fiddlehead Farm 10 years ago, and this is why we are back with North Tisbury Farm. It is also why I am asking you for help.   Our Vision: The Lath HouseNorth Tisbury Farm is looking to move further towards connecting with our community  through locally grown food. We are excited to present to you the concept of The Lath House.  A beautifully designed, open frame structure that makes you feel part of the garden AND part of the farm! The Lath House is a place where you can gather with friends and neighbors, or make new friends, and explore the many facets of food through our farm events, workshops, demos, tastings, and more.Growing a strong local food culture is at the core The Lath House concept, which will be:
A place to learn to grow, plant and harvest sustainably through our operations;
A place to learn from local foodies, experts, educators and artisans through workshops, lectures and more;
A place providing opportunities to all local growers, makers and bakers to showcase their talent and be an incubator of new start up ideas for the ever-growing demand for island-grown and sustainable products and ingredients;
A place to exchange ideas, inspire or be inspired by the island food production scene;

A place to collaborate with educational island programs;

A place with free workshops for the community;
A welcoming place for all ages.
Most importantly: we want you to feel at home and be a part of our vibrant community around island sourced food! Our PlanThe land North Tisbury Farm has a long history with agriculture. In 1938 Louis Greene ('old farmer Greene') took over the tiny three-acre farm that his father had bought in 1915, growing and selling vegetables. Most of the original farm is still intact, like our market building and one of the original old greenhouses which is still  in use. The location of the second original greenhouse -sadly torn down in the mid '90s - left a void on the property and is the proposed new site for The Lath House. We aim to welcome you at The Lath House at the beginning of next season 2019! Your helpWe aim to have The Lath House up by the beginning of next season (spring 2019). To make this happen we are looking to raise $50,000 in the next 30 days! Any amount helps.  With your support the funds raised will help with the critical cost of building a non-commercial space. This includes design plans, materials, labor, interior, landscaping, getting the word out, and more. Any amount raised over our goal will go towards funding workshops that will be offered to the community at no cost. We appreciate any and all contributions! As a thank you for your support we have selected some amazing incentives. Check them out in the sidebar.Not just the short term perksLong term, you're building into our island community. Your funding is a way to make a positive social impact on the sustainable local food systems. Through The Lath House you will be supporting local farmers, bakers, makers, food producers, vendors and artisans.Other Ways You Can HelpWe know that sometimes, making donations just isn’t an option. We understand that. You can still help by getting the word out about our campaign. Thank you for cross posting our campaign on social media feeds and tell others about our exciting plans.   Thank you!Rose Willett & the North Tisbury Farm team
